> ||'''Start Defenses''' ||||  %25color=red%25'''33.12'''%25%25%25 ||||||||%0a> ||'''End Defenses'''   ||||    12.44%25 ||||||||%0a> ||! Defensive Force ||||||||||||%0a> ||Unit ||   Start Quant. ||   End Quant. || Power ||  Armour || Shield ||%0a> ||Ion Turrets (5) || %25color=red%25'''1.66'''%25%25 || 0 || 48 || 67.2 || 3.4 ||%0a> ||Photon Turrets (20) || %25color=red%25'''6.63'''%25%25 || 0 || 92.8 || 134.4 || 10.2 ||%0a> ||Disruptor Turrets (15) || %25color=red%25'''4.97'''%25%25 || 1.51 || 281.6 || 537.6 || 13.6 ||%0a> ||Deflection Shields (10) || %25color=red%25'''3.32'''%25%25 || 2.26 || 3 || 1075.2 || 27.2 ||%0a> %0a> Therefore, Shields allow your base to fight longer than it might%0a> otherwise be able. Because the shields have the highest armour, their%0a> remaining armour regenerates the armour of the Plantary Rings and%0a> various Turrets. There is a consequence to this.%0a> %0a> Impact of Weaker Defenses%0a> ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~%0a> %0a> The weaker turrets drain the larger turrets because their start and end%0a> armour values are used to calculate the change in defenses; lowering the%0a> final result. Because they are more easily hit, they are always reduced%0a> to zero. %0a> %0a> In the series above, the attacker was able to use Fighters, Corvettes%0a> and Destroyers, all of which would have been combat ineffective against%0a> the Disruptor Turret, but they were quite effective against the weaker%0a> turrets. Because of the weaker turrets, an attacker can whittle away the%0a> strength of the Disrupter Turrets simply by leveling the Photon Turrets.%0a> %0a> The Photon Turrets above are seven percent of the total defensive%0a> strength; Ion and Photon Turrets together represent 11 percent. So with%0a> each successive wave, the attacker's weaker units could reduce the%0a> effectiveness of the more powerful turrets by 11 percent by reducing the%0a> weaker ones; even if they could not scratch the larger ones. %0a> %0a> What lesson can we learn from this? When you have Planetary Rings and%0a> Disruptor Turrets, the weaker shields (12.8 verse 19.2) of the Turrets%0a> would make the Planetary Rings vicariously vulnerable to weaker units.%0a> Therefore, when you have Planetary Rings, remove all Turrets.%0a> %0a> Have More Than Just Planetary Shields%0a> ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~%0a> %0a> Having the Planetary Shield as your only defense is also unwise. With%0a> the weak power in a Pshield, if it is your only defense, a single,%0a> patient Heavy Cruiser could effectively reduce your defenses piecemeal.%0a> Therefore, it is important to always have another base defense built in%0a> conjunction with the Shields.%0a
